│ // stores that can be put together into vector-stores. Next, it attempts to │
│ // construct vector operations that can be put between the consecutive      │
│ stores                                                                      │
│ // and the independent loads. This is an iterative process. The pass starts │
│ by                                                                          │
│ // finding all vectorizable stores and then builds up the graph of          │
│ dependent                                                                   │
│ // instructions. If a valid graph can be constructed, the instructions in   │
