│ first icmp produces all false values, while the second produces mixed values (<false, true>). The shufflevector selects element 0 from the first (false) and element 1 from the second (true), so the result   │
│ should be <false, true>. However, the optimization incorrectly returns zeroinitializer (<false, false>).                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The fix is to add conservative handling for shufflevector instructions in the InstCombine pass by implementing a visitShuffleVectorInst function that returns nullptr, preventing unsafe transformations that  │
│ could miscompile this pattern.                                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
